id takes precedence over classes
second class takes precedence over first class
in-line styles take first precedence over all css
add !important to style declaration to create top precedence
hex codes represent colors
red/green/blue, each gets two digits in #000000
0 is lowest, represents darkest
F is highest, represents brightest
black is #000000
white is #FFFFFF
brightest red #FF0000
brightest green #00FF00
brightest blue #0000FF
orange #FFA500
grey #808080
very dark grey, almost black #111111
can shorten hex code to three digits #000 (one per RGB)
shortened red #F00
can also use paranthetical rgb values - e.g. rgb(0, 0, 0)
specify brightness anywhere from 0 to 255
black is rgb(0, 0, 0)
white is rgb(255, 255, 255)
red is rgb(255, 0, 0)
green is rgb(0, 255, 0)
blue is rgb(0, 0, 255)
orange is rgb(255, 165, 0)
